comment: Enjoy the artwork outside the church on Pike, and check out some of the historical photos inside while you're there.

name: Planned Parenthood

comment: Ask the front desk for the key, you do not need to be a patient.

name: Bergen Community College Ender Hall

name: St. Paul's United Methodist Church
directions: Elevator access through first door from corner on Aurora St. Others enter through first set of double doors and go upstairs. Enter main hallway (behind sanctuary) and turn right. Bathrooms are down the hallway to the right with water fountains. Accessible single stall bathroom is first door on left of that hall, and includes a changing table and child size toilet as well.
comment: Check the website (http://www.stpaulsithaca.org/churches-near-me/churches-ithaca-ny/contact-us) or give a call to confirm that the building is open. Elevator use requires that the outside door be unlocked.

name: Chabot College
directions: Campus map lists locations of four gender neutral bathrooms on campus http://www.chabotcollege.edu/about/CampusMap.asp

name: Rosso Coffee Roasters
directions: Behind the pillar or the door on your left at the very back.
comment: Cafe staffed exclusively by LGBTQA+ and non binary people.

name: Rocky Mountain Biological Laboratory (RMBL)
directions: The public can use the outhouses straight back from the visitor center. There are also other outhouses up the road at the turnoff for the Judd Falls/Copper Creek Trailhead.
comment: All outhouses at RMBL are gender neutral.

name: YMCA
directions: Locker rooms are gendered but if you are a member, you can go upstairs and use the restroom outside the jogging track (elevator available).

name: Jesup Library
directions: Stairs are across from the circulation desk (stairs down are hiding under the stairs up). Go down and straight ahead is the restroom.
comment: Very friendly librarians won't mind if you come to take a pee.

name: Dorr Museum
directions: Go into the big room past the touch tank and take the doorway to the left.

name: St Andrews Public Library
directions: Take the door up to the stairs. The restroom is hiding halfway between floors. An elevator provides accessibility.

name: Rector's Cafe
directions: Using the side entry, go straight and look for the restroom on your right.
comment: Open for everyone, not just students.

name: Old Union Cafe
directions: Turn left at the counter, right through the arched stone vault, and through the white door. Each wood door conceals an independent restroom with sink, mirror, and toilet. The cafe is open to the public, not just students.
comment: The doors can stick sometimes so give them a bit of a push.

name: Boston University Questrom School of Business
directions: Fifth floor. Two units across from office #568.

name: Physics and Astronomy Building
street: University of St Andrews, North Haugh
directions: Through the large glass doors (handicap accessible button available) and to the left (towards the Eros cafe). Look for a door on the left near the bulletin boards.
comment: No student ID required to access the building during business hours.

name: Granite Peak Unitarian Congregation
comment: Inclusive congregation

name: Goodwill Career Center
comment: Lgbtq inclusive career center. The staff work with transgender people to get them jobs

name: pips original doughnuts
comment: two restrooms. gender neutral signs requested. the owner, nate, responded to say he would make the change.

name: Boston University Questrom School of Business
directions: Fifth floor. Get off elevator and two single unit restrooms are located behind you (take two rights or two lefts from the elevator). Located near office #568.

name: coffeehouse 5
comment: need key from coffee house

name: Washington and Lee University
directions: Elrod Commons has two all-gender single use bathrooms in the back hallway of the main floor, and the campus is generally a safe space for trans bathroom needs.
comment: If the building is unlocked, just go inside and use the bathroom. At night many doors (including to the Commons) get locked to non-University patrons, but people will generally let you in.

name: Countryside Gas & Grocery
directions: Straight ahead from the entrance, on the back wall.
comment: Single toilet gas station restroom with a locking door. This one is cleaner than most!

name: Corner Store / The Snappy Stop
directions: Straight ahead past the counter, on the right.
comment: Just a single toilet gas station restroom with a locking door.

name: Louisville Public Library
directions: Go to the second floor and take a right at the top of the staircase.

name: Strange Matter Coffee Co.
directions: In the back; what was the men's room is now marked as an all-gender restroom.
comment: It has a stall and a urinal, but there's a locking door for privacy.

name: IUPUI University Library
directions: on the 2nd floor, near the "Pop Shop", walk past the reference bookstacks, bathrooms will be on your right past a door labeled 2040 (with the librarians' offices)
comment: 2 separate bathrooms, please feel free to ask for directions at the Info Desk if you are comfortable

name: Boston University School of Theology
directions: First floor at the end of the hallway closest to the elevators. At the east end of the building. Single stall, gender neutral marked bathroom. Wheelchair ramp is behind the building, must go back at the west end of the building to access it. Take the elevator to the first floor.
comment: This is a BU graduate school but anyone may come in while the building is open.

name: The Coupe

comment: Please check in with the staff, especially during class times!  Restrooms are single occupancy.

name: Evanston Games & Café
directions: Two gender-neutral single stalls, across from the café bar.
comment: Freely available, no need to make a purchase.

name: The Bookloft
directions: Ask staff for directions to the restroom. They will lead you through their back room to a unisex customer restroom.
comment: No need to buy anything. Store is vocal about being a safe space.

name: Berkshire Museum
directions: There is a single stall / family style bathroom in the back of the first floor
comment: Will probably need to have been admission of ne a member, but ask at the front - the guest services are all very friendly

name: Flatiron Mall
directions:
There is one family restroom near the play area, with the gendered bathrooms. 
There is another, much quieter one in the strip mall area between the AMC Theater and the outdoor playground with the chess set. There is a bathroom sign outside. Go in, all the way back, turn left and keep going.
comment: I don't know if they are accessible. Getting a double stroller in wasn't easy.

name: Generic.Gallery
directions: Our public restroom is located in a secure hallway on the first floor next to our Gallery.
comment: Restroom is available during open studio and gallery hours which varies per exhibit. Our gallery/open studio is LGBTQIA+ friendly and genderqueer owned & operated.
